  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Completing the cycle for children on the streets: outreach - engagement - reintegration - prevention</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Life on the streets can be very harsh for street children, especially girls, and the risk of violence and abuse is a feature of daily life. This project uses surfing as a way to engage street children in Durban, South Africa, helping them to leave the streets, receive physical and emotional care and learn new skills to prepare them for the future. Wherever possible, street children are helped to return to their families and communities. Work is also done to prevent at-risk children leaving home and ending up living on the streets. As a result, children will be living in more stable environments, with improved confidence and well-being.</narrative>
  </description>
